N2  - This article reports on a longitudinal study of autonomous work groups at a new and an established minerals processing plant. The results of the study support the proposition that employees in autonomous work groups report more favorable work attitudes than their counterparts in traditionally designed jobs but confirm previous findings of higher absenteeism and turnover among autonomous work groups.
AB  - This article reports on a longitudinal study of autonomous work groups at a new and an established minerals processing plant. The results of the study support the proposition that employees in autonomous work groups report more favorable work attitudes than their counterparts in traditionally designed jobs but confirm previous findings of higher absenteeism and turnover among autonomous work groups.
