TY  - JOUR
T1  - Relationship of Career Mentoring and Socioeconomic Origin to Managers' and Professionals' Early Career Progress
AU  - Whitely, William
AU  - Dougherty, Thomas W.
AU  - Dreher, George F.
Y1  - 1991/06/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256445
DO  - 10.5465/256445
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 331
EP  - 350
VL  - 34
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the relationship of career mentoring to the promotions and compensation received by 404 early career managers and professionals working in a variety of organizations. The results indicate that with a number of variables controlled, career mentoring was related to both promotion rate and total compensation. The results also support the conclusion that career-oriented mentoring has a greater relationship with promotion rate for people from the highest-level socioeconomic backgrounds than for those from lower-level backgrounds. We provide several explanations for the effects of career mentoring on early career progress and suggest a number of areas for future research on mentoring and other developmental relationships.
AB  - This study examined the relationship of career mentoring to the promotions and compensation received by 404 early career managers and professionals working in a variety of organizations. The results indicate that with a number of variables controlled, career mentoring was related to both promotion rate and total compensation. The results also support the conclusion that career-oriented mentoring has a greater relationship with promotion rate for people from the highest-level socioeconomic backgrounds than for those from lower-level backgrounds. We provide several explanations for the effects of career mentoring on early career progress and suggest a number of areas for future research on mentoring and other developmental relationships.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256445
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256445
Y2  - 2026/04/24
